---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About Shingai Thornton and Halcyonic Systems">
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-16">
    <h1 class="ab-title">About</h1>

    <div class="ab-intro">
      <div class="ab-kingfisher">
        <img src="/logo.png" alt="Halcyonic kingfisher" class="ab-bird" />
      </div>
      <div class="ab-story">
        <p>
          The halcyon is the kingfisher of Greek myth — the bird that nests on calm seas.
          Ancient sailors believed it could still the waves during its brooding days, creating
          a window of peace in the middle of winter storms. That stillness is what we pursue:
          a point of formal rigor in the chaos of transdisciplinary complexity.
          The stillness isn't about the work being calm. It's about what internalizing
          systems concepts does to the person holding the lens.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ab-bio">
      <p>
        I'm Shingai Thornton, founder of Halcyonic Systems. We build tools that help people reason about complex systems.
      </p>
      <p>
        In 2017, I stumbled across <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Principles-Systems-Science-Understanding-Complex/dp/1493919199" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">systems science</a>, a field that promised to ground my work
        across every domain I'd touched and give me the scaffolding to learn sciences I'd
        written off as beyond my reach. I quickly discovered that the field barely exists,
        other than as a <a href="https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/full/10.1002/sres.2215" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">fragmented set of theories, frameworks, and methodologies</a>. So I
        started learning and building: the theory, the tools, and the infrastructure
        necessary to integrate the fractured systems sciences.
      </p>
      <p>
        What I do day-to-day: take abstract ideas and turn them into interactive models, software,
        and visualizations that make those ideas more real. Usually for myself, to better understand
        something I couldn't otherwise. Sometimes for clients. Always toward making rigorous systems
        reasoning more broadly accessible. A growing part of Halcyonic's work is building infrastructure that
        makes LLMs useful: structured ontologies, retrieval pipelines, and fine-tuned models
        trained on formal systems science.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="ab-lineage">
      <h2 class="ab-section-header">Intellectual Lineage</h2>
      <dl class="ab-lineage-list">
        <div class="ab-lineage-entry">
          <dt>Mobus</dt>
          <dd>Systems science is a real discipline worth a life's work.</dd>
        </div>
        <div class="ab-lineage-entry">
          <dt>Joslyn</dt>
          <dd>Mathematics isn't notation and numbers, it's a language precise enough to say what systems actually are.</dd>
        </div>
        <div class="ab-lineage-entry">
          <dt>Bunge</dt>
          <dd>Philosophical clarity and mathematical precision are the same demand. Their absence may be why general systems theory fragmented.</dd>
        </div>
        <div class="ab-lineage-entry">
          <dt>Bertalanffy</dt>
          <dd>Fragmentation of the sciences has diminishing returns. Thinking in wholes has barely begun.</dd>
        </div>
      </dl>
    </div>

    <!-- CommutingTriangle hidden 2026-04-28: Labs/Ventures vertices not yet operational.
         Resurface when all three layers have substance, or reframe as pure theoretical result
         (Klir→Bunge→Mobus convergence) without the org structure overlay.
         Component lives at src/components/CommutingTriangle.astro -->


    <div class="ab-connect">
      <h2 class="ab-section-header">Connect</h2>
      <div class="ab-links">
        <a href="mailto:shingai@halcyonic.systems" class="ab-link">
          shingai@halcyonic.systems <span aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span>
        </a>
        <a href="https://github.com/halcyonic-systems" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="ab-link">
          GitHub <span aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span>
        </a>
<a href="https://ideas.halcyonic.systems" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="ab-link">
          Substack <span aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .ab-title {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--color-frost-slate);
  }

  .ab-intro {
    display: flex;
    gap: 2rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .ab-kingfisher {
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .ab-bird {
    width: 140px;
    height: 140px;
    border-radius: 12px;
    object-fit: cover;
  }

  .ab-story {
    flex: 1;
  }

  .ab-story p {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', Georgia, serif;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-frost-slate-dim);
  }

  .ab-bio {
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
  }

  .ab-bio a {
    color: var(--color-frost-teal);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-decoration-color: rgba(13, 148, 136, 0.3);
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
    transition: text-decoration-color 0.2s ease;
  }

  .ab-bio a:hover {
    text-decoration-color: var(--color-frost-teal);
  }

  .ab-bio p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-frost-slate-dim);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .ab-section-header {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.6rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-frost-teal-dim);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .ab-lineage, .ab-architecture {
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    padding-top: 1.5rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-frost-border);
  }

  .ab-lineage-list {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .ab-lineage-entry {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    align-items: baseline;
  }

  .ab-lineage-entry dt {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    min-width: 6.5rem;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .ab-lineage-entry:nth-child(1) dt { color: var(--color-frost-teal); }
  .ab-lineage-entry:nth-child(2) dt { color: var(--color-frost-indigo); }
  .ab-lineage-entry:nth-child(3) dt { color: var(--color-frost-rose); }
  .ab-lineage-entry:nth-child(4) dt { color: var(--color-frost-amber); }

  .ab-lineage-entry dd {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-frost-slate-dim);
  }

  .ab-connect {
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    padding-top: 1.5rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-frost-border);
  }

  .ab-links {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .ab-link {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--color-frost-teal);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: opacity 0.2s ease;
  }

  .ab-link:hover {
    opacity: 0.7;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .ab-intro {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
      text-align: center;
    }
  }
</style>
